A4.text: The Canada–United States Free Trade Agreement (CUSFTA), official name as the Free Trade Agreement between Canada and the United States of America (French: Accord de libre-échange entre le Canada et les États-Unis d'Amérique), was a bilateral trade agreement reached by negotiators for Canada and the United States.

A5.text: With the addition of Mexico in 1994, CUSFTA was superseded by the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA)
